#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:5
msgid "Configuring Emscripten Settings when Manually Building from Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:7
msgid ""
"Emscripten can be configured via a :ref:`compiler configuration file (."
"emscripten) <compiler-configuration-file>`. These settings include paths to "
"the tools (LLVM, Clang, Binaryen, etc.) and the compiler's temporary "
"directory for intermediate build files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:12
msgid ""
"This configuration file is optional.  By default, emscripten will search for "
"the tools it needs in the ``PATH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:15
msgid ""
"This article explains how to create and update the file when you are "
"building Emscripten :ref:`manually <installing-from-source>` from source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:20
msgid "Creating the compiler configuration file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:22
msgid ""
"A settings file may be used when running :ref:`emcc <emccdoc>` (or any of "
"the other Emscripten tools).  You can run ``emcc`` with ``--generate-"
"config`` in order to generate one in the default location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:26
msgid "Navigate to the directory where you cloned the Emscripten repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:27
msgid "Enter the command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:33
msgid ""
"You should get a ``An Emscripten settings file has been generated at:`` "
"message, along with the contents of the config file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:36
msgid ""
"When generating this file Emscripten will make its \"best guess\" at the "
"correct locations for tools based on the current ``PATH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:39
msgid ""
"In most cases it will be necessary to edit the generated file and modify "
"least the ``LLVM_ROOT`` and ``BINARYEN_ROOT`` settings to point to the "
"correct locations for your local LLVM and Binaryen installations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:45
msgid "Locating the compiler configuration file (.emscripten)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:47
msgid ""
"The settings file (``.emscripten``) is created by default within the "
"emscripten directory (alongside ``emcc`` itself).  In cases where the "
"emscripten directory is read-only the user's home directory will be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:51
msgid ""
"On Linux and macOS this file is named **~/.emscripten**, where ~ is the "
"user's home directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:54
msgid ""
"Files with the \".\" prefix are hidden by default. You may need to change "
"your view settings to find the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:56
msgid ""
"On Windows the file can be found at a path like: **C:/Users/"
"yourusername_000/.emscripten**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:60
msgid "Compiler configuration file-format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:62
msgid ""
"While the syntax is identical, the appearance of the default **.emscripten** "
"file created by *emcc* is quite different than that created by :ref:`emsdk "
"<compiler-configuration-file>`. This is because *emsdk* manages multiple "
"target environments, and where possible hard codes the locations of those "
"tools when a new environment is activated. The default file, by contrast, is "
"managed by the user — and is designed to make that task as easy as possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:64
msgid ""
"The file simply assigns values to a number of *variables* representing the "
"main tools used by Emscripten. For example, if your binaryen installation is "
"in **C:\\\\tools\\\\binaryen\\\\**, then the file might contain the line: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:70
msgid ""
"You can find out the other variable names from the default *.emscripten* "
"file or the :ref:`example here <compiler-configuration-file>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:74
msgid "Editing the compiler configuration file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:76
msgid ""
"The compiler configuration file can be edited with the text editor of your "
"choice. If you're building manually from source, you are most likely to have "
"to update the variable ``LLVM_ROOT``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:80
msgid ""
"Edit the variable ``LLVM_ROOT`` to point to the directory where you built "
"the LLVM binaries, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:87
msgid "Use forward slashes!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/configuring_emscripten_settings.rst:89
msgid ""
"After setting those paths, run ``emcc`` again. It should again perform the "
"sanity checks to test the specified paths. There are further validation "
"tests available at :ref:`verifying-the-emscripten-environment`."
msgstr ""
